2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 208
BY REPRESENTATIVE DICKERSON
A RESOLUTION
To urge and request the Department of Transportation and Development to construct a
roundabout on Louisiana Highway 1019 near Old Louisiana Highway 16.
WHEREAS, roundabouts can improve the safety, operations, and aesthetics of an
intersection; and
WHEREAS, according to the Federal Highway Administration, roundabouts save
lives by reducing fatalities by up to ninety percent by reducing injury crashes up to seventy-
six percent and pedestrian crashes up to forty percent; and
WHEREAS, a traditional four-way intersection has thirty-two potential vehicle
conflict points, however, a single-lane roundabout has only eight, significantly lowering the
chance of collisions; and
WHEREAS, the circular design virtually eliminates high-speed, head-on, and
"T-bone" (right-angle) collisions, which are the most deadly types of intersection accidents;
and
WHEREAS, the shape of roundabouts forces drivers to slow to fifteen to twenty-five
miles per hour, which affords drivers more time to react to other road users and making any
resulting crashes far less severe; and
WHEREAS, there is only a stop sign on Louisiana Highway 1019 (LA-1019) at the
intersection of Old Louisiana Highway 16 (Old LA-16), resulting in a lack of traffic
regulation; and
WHEREAS, speed limits in the area range from twenty-five to thirty-five miles per
hour; and
